red tail reborn is a 2007 historical documentary film by adam white about the commemorative air force 's red tail project . the project involves the restoration , exhibition and maintenance of a world war ii p-51 mustang flown by the united states air force 332d fighter group . the exhibition of this plane is considered to be a traveling and flying tribute to the tuskegee airmen . in addition to increasing awareness of the travails of the tuskegee airmen , this film served to highlight the red tail project fundraising effort to rebuild the plane after a 2004 crash . the film was initially broadcast and released on dvd in 2007 in the director 's home state of ohio , winning local emmy award recognition . the following year , it was broadcast nationally for the first time on public broadcasting services ( pbs ) stations . the film had a sequel called flight of the red tail .